page.title: 12HOUSING IN WEST HULL
page.content: West Hull is a mainly residential area with various different types of housing. Boulevard-large Victorian houses along a tree lined avenue. Some are now split into flats. Anlaby Park-private semi-detached and detached houses arranged around a central green and library.An attractive area with quiet roads and a lot of trees.Large gardens and garages.Built in the 1930s. The Greenway is an open grassy area on an old council estate. Mainly terraced houses.Over 200 of these houses are now being modernised with new bathrooms,windows and central heating. Rokeby Close.A concil estate built in the 1950s.Brick,terraced housing. Near to the docks the terraced housing is waiting for demolition.
